Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with fixpoint extensions of first-order logic and automata on trees, which are topics closely related to logic. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper introduces a new class of parity automata and discusses their expressive power. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of various logics and automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the expressiveness of various logics and automata on trees, which can be seen as a data structure. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the expressiveness of logics and automata, which are relevant to the study of artificial intelligence.
